-- India’s Tamil Nadu State Utility Seeks 3.7 Million Tons of Coal
-- B y   A r c h a n a   C h a u d h a r y
-- 2013-11-12T10:22:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-11-12/india-s-tamil-nadu-state-utility-seeks-3-7-million-tons-of-coal.html
India ’s  Tamil Nadu Generation &
Distribution Corp.  is seeking 3.7 million metric tons of power-station coal for delivery from March to August of 2014.  The state utility, based in the southern Indian city of
Chennai, is seeking 2.8 million metric tons of thermal coal to
be delivered to Ennore and Karaikal, as well as 900,000 tons to
Tuticorin, according to a tender  document  posted on the
company’s website.  Tamil Nadu is seeking coal with calorific value of 6,000
kilocalories a kilogram and total moisture and sulfur content of
15 percent and 6 percent, respectively. Offers are due Dec. 6.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Archana Chaudhary in  New Delhi  at 
